> Our Thai Green Style Tofu Curry is a delicious veggie option that makes it easy to eat more
> veg in your diet and try something new!

Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{3}(peeled) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Pour the @water{300%ml} into a #medium saucepan{} with a tight-fitting #lid{}.
Stir in the @jasmine rice{150%g}, half the garlic and @salt{1/4%tsp} and bring to the boil.
Once boiling, turn the heat down to medium and cover with the lid.

Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and leave
to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook
in its own steam).

Drain the @firm tofu{280%g} and chop into 2cm cubes. Pat dry with #kitchen paper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @oil in a #large frying pan{} on high heat.
Once hot, fry the tofu until slightly crispy, ~{8-10%minutes}. Turn frequently to ensure
they don't burn.

Meanwhile, trim the @green beans{80%g}, then cut into thirds. Zest and halve the
@lime{1/2}.

Once the tofu is crispy, turn the heat down to medium and add the green beans, garlic
and @Indonesian style spice mix{1}. Toss to coat evenly and cook for ~{30%seconds}.

Stir the @Thai green curry paste{45%g} into the pan and cook for ~{30%seconds}.

Pour in the @coconut milk{200%ml} and @water{100%ml}, stir together, then mix in the
@vegetable stock paste{10%g}.

Bring to the boil, then turn the heat down to medium and simmer the curry until
thickened slightly, ~{5-7%minutes}.

When the curry has thickened, taste and season with @salt{}, @ground black pepper{} and
a squeeze of @lime juice{} from the remaining half lime.

Add a splash of water if it's a little too thick, then remove from the heat.

Fluff up the rice with a #fork{} and stir through the lime zest.

Share the rice and tofu curry between your #bowls{}. Serve with any remaining lime
wedges on the side for squeezing over.

Enjoy!